# Card Data: Cache-First Over Scryfall

For any card-related implementation (lookups, images, metadata, search, validation), **prefer `scryfall_cache` before calling Scryfall API**.

## Why

- Reduces Scryfall API usage and rate-limit risk
- Faster responses (DB vs external network)
- Improves backfill/scripts performance when processing many decks

## Available Helpers

| Need | Use | Location |
|------|-----|----------|
| Images (small, normal, art_crop) | `getImagesForNamesCached(names)` | `@/lib/server/scryfallCache` |
| Full details (type_line, oracle_text, color_identity, etc.) | `getDetailsForNamesCached(names)` | `@/lib/server/scryfallCache` |
| Cache-only read (no Scryfall fetch) | `getDetailsForNamesCacheOnly(names)` | `@/lib/server/scryfallCache` |
| Profile/trends data | `getCardDataForProfileTrends(names)` | `@/lib/server/scryfallCache` |

## Pattern

1. Query `scryfall_cache` by normalized name
2. Use cache hits immediately
3. Only call Scryfall API for misses (and optionally upsert into cache for next time)

## Normalization

Cache uses **normalized names** (lowercase, NFKD, no diacritics, collapsed spaces):

```typescript
function norm(s: string) {
  return String(s || "").toLowerCase().normalize("NFKD")
    .replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "")
    .replace(/\s+/g, " ")
    .trim();
}
```

## Standalone Scripts

Scripts (e.g. `scripts/*.ts`) use Supabase directly. Query `scryfall_cache` first with `.in("name", normalizedNames)`, then call Scryfall only for misses.
